criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Had a stroke or transient ischemic attack (TIA) or was the informal carer of a person
             who had a stroke or TIA;

          -  Had a reported English-proficiency level, corrected hearing and vision, and
             communication status adequate to participate in an interview and complete assessment
             tasks;

          -  Did not have reported or observable dementia;

          -  Lived within 50km of the hospital, for ease of follow-up; and

          -  Was medically stable.
